    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but i'm so tired of trying. every morning i just feel like i'm performing a role in a play that ended months ago. i go through the motions, i eat the food, i do the laundry... but it feels so fake. like i'm just a ghost haunting my own life. it's exhausting to pretend that there's actually something to look forward to when the only person who made it worth it is gone. it feels like i'm just dragging this heavy, empty shell around for no reason.",
